<TITLE> Businessman Abdus Salam becomes new CDA chairman </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 23 (bdnews24.com)  Abdus Salam, chairman of the Well Group of Industries, has been appointed new chief of the Chittagong Development Authority. The government has appointed the local business leader as chairman of the port city's development authority on a contractual basis for the next two years. His appointment will be effected from the date of his joining, said an order ministry of establishment on Thursday. bdn
